            "title": "U.S. Factory Orders Unchanged in February",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Don Nico Forbes </p><br/><p>\n   U.S. factory orders held steady in February, the Census Bureau said Friday, pointing to a lull in activity before the outbreak of war in Iran. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  Orders from U.S. factories were unchanged in the month at $619.6 billion. A consensus of economists polled by The Wall Street Journal expected a 0.1% fall. </p><p>\n\n  The report showed that shipments from factories increased 1.4%. Unfilled orders rose 0.1%, the report said. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Don Nico Forbes at don.forbes@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  04-10-26 1026ET</p></div>",
